data.text: HM DIPLOMATIC SERVICE OVERSEAS REFERENCE LIST PART I. EMBASSIES, HIGH COMMISSIONS, DEPUTY HIGH COMMISSIONS & CONSULAR POSTS. PART II. MISSIONS & DELEGATIONS PART III. GOVERNORS & COMMANDERS-IN-CHIEF OF THE UK OVERSEAS TERRITORIES PART IV. SMALL POSTS & ANNEX July/August 2004 This list is issued by the Foreign & Commonwealth Office in January & July/August of each year. It is as up to date as possible & is based on information available at the time of going to print, i.e. EARLY NOVEMBER & EARLY MAY RESPECTIVELY. The deadline for amendments to the next edition can be found below. Place names are in accordance with those given in the Foreign & Commonwealth Office Publication ‘Geographical Names & Information’ available from Library E-Services Team and is also on the FCO Website. AMENDMENTS should be written on a copy of the current issue & sent or faxed to THE EDITOR, PUBLICATIONS, ROOM WH MZ 11, E-SERVICES, LIBRARY & INFORMATION SERVICES, INFORMATION MANAGEMENT DEPARTMENT, FOREIGN & COMMONWEALTH OFFICE LONDON SW1A 2AH. (FAX NUMBER: 020 7008 3802). DEADLINE for amendments for the January 2005 edition will be C.O.P FRIDAY, 8th OCTOBER 2004. Please note that the Editor will no longer be issuing circulars or sending e-mails in order to remind Management Officers to send in their amendments. Instead, Management Officers can find information about completing their amendments on the next page of this issue and future issues. COPIES can be requested by faxing Teresa Fernandes (Assistant Editor) on the number above or by e-mail to (Teresa.Fernandes@fco.gov.uk) (Staff from other Government Departments & Agencies should obtain copies from their libraries) Please inform the Assistant Editor of any change of address to which copies should be sent. Undelivered copies should be returned to the Assistant Editor. CROWN COPYRIGHT 2004
